 </p>
 <p>Multiplying U,Σ and V may not give the original matrix A, due to the sign ambiguity problem</p>
 <p>
 </p>
 <p>
  <b>Inverse</b>
  (
  <em>matrix</em>
  )
 </p>
 <hr/>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   =
   <span class="b0">[</span>
   4; 12; -16
   <span class="b0">|</span>
   12; 37; -43
   <span class="b0">|</span>
   -16; -43; 98
   <span class="b0">]</span>
   =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">4</span>
     <span class="td">12</span>
     <span class="td">-16</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">12</span>
     <span class="td">37</span>
